ntent%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20celebrating%20the%20holidays.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6753219c8fbb2783ed3041c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELehel%20Kov%C3%A1cs%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20corporate%20bosses%2C%20associates%2C%20and%20interns%20alike%20would%20set%20aside%20their%20different%20titles%20and%20gather%20each%20December%20for%20drinks%2C%20dancing%2C%20and%20conversation.%20There%20would%20be%20gourmet%20dinners%2C%20chocolate%20fountains%2C%20DJs%2C%20and%20even%20live%20bands.%20For%20some%2C%20it%20was%20a%20night%20of%20merriment%20and%20splendor%3B%20for%20others%2C%20of%20awkward%20small%20talk%2C%20followed%20by%20deep%20regret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20holiday%20party%20became%20endangered.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20%23MeToo%20in%202017%2C%20more%20professionals%20began%20rethinking%20the%20wisdom%20of%20a%20boozed-up%20night%20with%20their%20colleagues.%20The%20pandemic%20and%20remote%20work%20delivered%20a%20near%20death%20blow.%20In%20a%202020%20survey%20of%20about%20200%20HR%20representatives%20by%20the%20executive-outplacement%20firm%20Challenger%2C%20Gray%20%26amp%3B%20Christmas%2C%20a%20mere%2023%25%20said%20they%20opted%20for%20seasonal%20celebrations%2C%20nearly%20three-quarters%20of%20which%20would%20be%20held%20virtually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20return%20to%20offices%20continues%2C%20companies%20are%20slowly%20reinstituting%20holiday%20parties.%20Last%20year%2C%20nearly%2065%25%20of%20companies%20surveyed%20by%20Challenger%2C%20Gray%2C%20%26amp%3B%20Christmas%20said%20they%20planned%20to%20host%20in-person%20holiday%20parties%2C%20within%20sight%20of%20the%2080%25%20reported%20in%202016%2C%20before%20the%20advent%20of%20%23MeToo.%20If%20plans%20pan%20out%2C%20this%20year%20could%20have%20before-times%20levels%20of%20corporate%20holiday%20cheer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20return%20of%20the%20office%20holiday%20party%20could%20be%20a%20happier%20development%20than%20many%20jaded%20workers%20are%20likely%20inclined%20to%20presume.%20With%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20American%20white-collar%20workforce%20working%20remotely%20either%20some%20or%20all%20of%20the%20time%2C%20according%20to%20a%20USA%20Today%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fmoney%2Fblueprint%2Fbusiness%2Fhr-payroll%2Fremote-work-statistics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20face%20time%20with%20colleagues%20and%20superiors%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20default%20feature%20of%20the%209-to-5.%20That%20might%20not%20be%20a%20big%20deal%20for%20everyone%2C%20but%20early-career%20workers%20stand%20to%20pay%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-gen-z-loneliness-heading-returning-to-office-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esteepest%20professional%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20missing%20out%20on%20the%20kinds%20of%20networking%20and%20mentorship%20opportunities%20that%20are%20likelier%20to%20happen%20organically%20in%20a%20shared%20physical%20space.%20All%20the%20while%2C%20workers%20across%20the%20board%20are%20feeling%20increasingly%20lonely%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-engagement-productivity-remote-work-hybrid-burnout-managers-office-expectations-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverextended%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-detachment-is-looming-for-employees-especially-for-gen-z-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisengaged%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20need%20something%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Eanything%20%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20celebrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20work%20environment%20punctuated%20by%20uncertainty%20and%20isolation%2C%20it%20might%20be%20premature%20to%20let%20one's%20inner%20Scrooge%20have%20the%20final%20word%20on%20the%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Fezziwig's%20ball%20in%20%26quot%3BA%20Christmas%20Carol%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20power-suited%20backdrop%20of%20the%201988%20Christmas%20Eve%20action%20thriller%20%26quot%3BDie%20Hard%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20workplace%20holiday%20party%20has%20been%20a%20fixture%20of%20the%20cultural%20imagination%20for%20generations.%20But%20in%20the%20mid-20th%20century%2C%20the%20event%20garnered%20its%20enduring%20reputation%20for%20sloppiness%20and%20day-after%20regret.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.life.com%2Flifestyle%2Fletting-loose-at-work-life-goes-to-an-office-party%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1948%20Life%20magazine%20photo%20spread%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20Christmas%20party%20thrown%20in%20the%20office%20of%20a%20Manhattan%20insurance%20brokerage%20depicts%2C%20among%20other%20modern-day%20HR%20violations%2C%20a%20pantless%20male%20executive%20dancing%20arm%20in%20arm%20with%20a%20young%20female%20stenographer%20and%20a%20pair%20of%20colleagues%20leaning%20in%20for%20a%20smooch%20beneath%20a%20bundle%20of%20mistletoe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomewhere%20along%20the%20way%2C%20festivities%20evolved%20from%20low-key%20gatherings%20held%20at%20the%20office%20to%20lavish%20affairs%20that%20might%20include%20gourmet%20meals%2C%20hired%20entertainment%2C%20and%20even%20international%20travel%20and%20accommodation%20on%20the%20boss'%20dime.%20The%20pandemic%20notwithstanding%2C%20the%20economic%20pendulum%20has%20largely%20dictated%20its%20tilt%20toward%20excess%20or%20restraint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20Toronto-area%20DJ%20during%20the%20halcyon%20days%20of%20the%20late-'90s%20dot-com%20bubble%2C%20Baruch%20Labunski%20had%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20corporate-party%20splendor.%20%26quot%3BI%20went%20to%20many%20and%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20crazy%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20described%20being%20flown%20to%20DJ%20holiday%20parties%20in%20far-flung%20global%20destinations%20such%20as%20Bora%20Bora%2C%20Palawan%2C%20and%20Ibiza%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20on%20top%20of%20that%2C%20getting%20paid%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%24100%2C000%20per%20event.%20(When%20I%20asked%20how%20many%20holiday%20parties%20he%20booked%20in%20a%20typical%20season%2C%20he%20said%20only%20%26quot%3Bmany.%26quot%3B)%20By%20the%20time%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20burst%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20his%20services%20cooled%2C%20Labunski%20had%20tired%20himself%20out%20of%20the%20DJ%20booth%20and%20pivoted%20to%20a%20career%20in%20marketing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomic%20recovery%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%20spurred%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworst-year-corporate-holiday-parties-2010-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eholiday-party%20renaissance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20to%20be%20dashed%20once%20again%20in%20the%202008%20recession.%20A%20few%20years%20later%2C%20Wall%20Street%20firms%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-usa-wall-street-parties%2Fwall-street-holiday-parties-are-back-but-dont-tell-anyone-idUSKBN14B0FI%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20to%20enjoying%20hush-hush%20holiday%20festivities%20reminiscent%20of%20their%20heydays.%20The%20free-money%20firehose%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F90-of-the-industrialized-world-right-anchored-by-zirp-2015-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20ZIRP%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20in%20full%20force%2C%20and%20excess%20was%20back%20in%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Kane%2C%20who%20was%20a%20reporter%20for%20a%20niche%20New%20York%20City%20financial-services%20publication%20between%202015%20and%202017%2C%20said%20that%20one%20year%20her%20company%20flew%20the%20entire%20staff%20of%2050%20to%2075%20people%20to%20Berlin.%20%26quot%3BHotels%20and%20flights%20were%20paid%20for%2C%20there%20was%20an%20experiential%20dinner%20at%20the%20Berlin%20TV%20Tower%2C%20and%20then%20they%20paid%20for%20everyone%20to%20get%20into%20a%20fancy%20club%20afterwards%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20late%20night%2C%20and%20I've%20never%20experienced%20a%20company%20holiday%20party%20like%20it%20since.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20their%20fun%2C%20these%20often%20cringe-inducing%20affairs%20earned%20a%20bad%20rap%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20may%20come%20to%20bite%20younger%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20some%20companies'%20largesse%2C%20the%20general%20workforce's%20enthusiasm%20for%20holiday%20parties%20has%20long%20been%20mixed.%20In%20a%202017%20survey%20of%20American%20workers%20by%20Randstad%2C%2090%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they'd%20rather%20receive%20bonuses%20or%20extra%20vacation%20days%20than%20attend%20a%20company%20holiday%20party.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ideal%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Constance%20Noonan%20Hadley%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20to%20offer%20activities%20that%20foster%20employee%20social%20health%20(such%20as%20a%20holiday%20party)%20without%20asking%20them%20to%20sacrifice%20their%20financial%20health%20(such%20as%20a%20bonus)%20or%20their%20mental%20health%20(such%20as%20time%20off).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20squander%20the%20opportunity%20to%20make%20holiday%20gatherings%20meaningful%20in%20all%20sorts%20of%20small%20but%20critical%20ways.%20Hadley%20said%20the%20Christmas-specific%20focus%20of%20many%20company%20holiday%20parties%20could%20be%20alienating%20to%20workers%20who%20follow%20non-Christian%20religious%20traditions.%20Parties%20are%20often%20held%20at%20inconvenient%20times%20and%20places%20%E2%80%94%20too%20late%20on%20a%20weeknight%20for%20parents%2C%20in%20a%20location%20that%20has%20expensive%20parking%20or%20is%20hard%20to%20access.%20Holiday%20parties%20at%20big%20firms%20can%20also%20be%20loud%2C%20hot%2C%20and%20crowded%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20have%20meaningful%20conversations%20or%20meet%20new%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell-planned%20company%20holiday%20parties%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20can%20be%20a%20boon%20to%20employees'%20overall%20work%20experience%20and%20even%20strengthen%20company%20culture.%20A%20study%20of%20workers%20at%20several%20German%20companies%20in%202019%20concluded%20that%20parties%20could%20encourage%20social%20bonding%2C%20especially%20when%20employees'%20feedback%20steered%20the%20planning.%20The%20study%20suggests%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20icebreaker%20activities%20that%20get%20people%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20organization%20talking%20help%20build%20camaraderie%2C%20despite%20the%20eye%20rolls%20they%20may%20initially%20provoke.%20Over%20time%2C%20that%20can%20contribute%20to%20a%20happier%20and%20more%20cohesive%20work%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20early-career%20workers%2C%20the%20benefits%20can%20be%20more%20pronounced.%20Rick%20Hermanns%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20HireQuest%2C%20a%20global%20staffing%20company%2C%20said%20social%20events%20could%20help%20make%20up%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bintangible%20aspects%20of%20career%20growth%20and%20camaraderie%20between%20colleagues%26quot%3B%20that%20younger%20workers%20may%20miss%20out%20on%20when%20they're%20partly%20or%20fully%20remote.%20In%20a%202023%20Adobe%20poll%20of%20more%20than%201%2C000%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20at%20midsize%20and%20large%20US%20companies%2C%2083%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20a%20workplace%20mentor%20was%20crucial%20for%20their%20career%2C%20but%20only%2052%25%20said%20they%20had%20one.%20While%20holiday%20parties%20aren't%20the%20be-all%20and%20end-all%20of%20workplace%20networking%2C%20they%20provide%20a%20critical%20opening%20to%20build%20and%20fortify%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20look%20back%20at%20my%20early%20career%20in%20banking%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20I%20appreciated%20the%20time%20I%20had%20to%20walk%20into%20a%20senior%20executive's%20office%20or%20grab%20a%20beer%20after%20work%20with%20colleagues%2C%26quot%3B%20Hermanns%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20intangibles%20you%20can't%20quantify%20yet%20ultimately%20impact%20your%20career%20growth.%26quot%3B%20Simply%20put%2C%20face%20time%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense%20that%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20workers%20would%20be%20more%20enthusiastic%20about%20workplace%20holiday%20get-togethers%20than%20their%20Gen%20X%20and%20baby-boomer%20counterparts.%20%26quot%3BCompany%20leaders%20need%20to%20help%20Gen%20Z%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20millennials%2C%20whose%20workplace%20experience%20was%20hugely%20disrupted%20by%20COVID%20%E2%80%94%20to%20build%20strong%20interpersonal%20workplace%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20Hubert%20Palan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20product-management%20company%20Productboard%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-gen-z-loneliness-heading-returning-to-office-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20much%20of%20the%20global%20workforce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F645566%2Femployees-worldwide-feel-lonely.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeels%20lonely%20on%20the%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20the%20youngest%20workers%20who%20need%20a%20social%20boost.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.institutelifework.org%2Four-research%23work-loneliness-relationships%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20study%20Hadley%20coauthored%3C%2Fa%3E%20evaluating%20workplace%20loneliness%20and%20remedies%20found%20that%20the%20loneliest%20people%20at%20work%20were%20those%20who%20were%20offered%20the%20fewest%20social%20opportunities%20by%20their%20employer.%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20the%20number%20of%20social%20offerings%20provided%20was%20one%20of%20our%20most%20predictive%20variables%20in%20terms%20of%20whether%20someone%20was%20socially%20connected%20at%20work%20or%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20Hadley%20also%20found%20that%20while%20fully%20remote%20work%20did%20seem%20to%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20loneliness%2C%20it%20was%20less%20significant%20of%20a%20variable%20than%20whether%20a%20person%20was%20introverted%20or%20worked%20for%20an%20organization%20that%20held%20regular%20social%20activities%20for%20staffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20study%20suggests%20that%20a%20holiday%20party%20can%20serve%20as%20the%20ritual%20capstone%20for%20these%20more%20routine%20coworker%20events%2C%20making%20year-end%20hobnobbing%20just%20a%20little%20extra%20special.%20While%20the%20ideal%20party%20activities%20will%20depend%20on%20an%20organization's%20culture%2C%20a%20few%20basic%20considerations%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20hosting%20the%20event%20somewhere%20besides%20the%20boring%20old%20office%20%E2%80%94%20go%20a%20long%20way.%20Elements%20of%20fun%20help%20too%2C%20whether%20they%20take%20the%20form%20of%20a%20themed%20photo%20booth%2C%20a%20creative%20dining%20experience%2C%20or%2C%20yes%2C%20a%20DJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20dash%20of%20festive%20foresight%20can%20make%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20raunchy%20affairs%20of%20yesteryear%20and%20a%20few%20hours%20of%20meaningful%2C%20PG-rated%20bonding%20between%20coworkers.%20%26quot%3BA%20nice%20holiday%20event%20gives%20people%20a%20break%20in%20their%20wallets%20and%20signals%20that%20the%20leaders%20value%20personal%20connections%20and%20socializing%2C%26quot%3B%20Hadley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20company's%20youngest%20workers%2C%20the%20benefits%20may%20last%20a%20professional%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EKelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20work%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20culture.%20She's%20based%20in%20New%20York%20Ci