asn't%20going%20to%20go%20anywhere%20after%20graduation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20thought%2C%20might%20as%20well%20apply%2C%20and%20we'll%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20classes%2C%20you%20know%2C%20do%20something%20better%20with%20my%20time%20during%20this%20period.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessor%20David%20Garlan%2C%20the%20associate%20dean%20for%20Carnegie%20Mellon's%20computer%20science%20master's%20program%2C%20said%20that%20while%20the%20university%20hasn't%20seen%20a%20notable%20increase%20in%20CS%20grad%20enrollment%2C%20other%20schools%20with%20less%20selective%20and%20extensive%20programs%20may%20experience%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20true%20that%20when%20the%20economy%20has%20a%20downturn%2C%20people%20go%20back%20to%20education%20because%20they're%20not%20able%20to%20find%20jobs%20so%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20there%20is%20definitely%20that%20trend%2C%20overall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnrollment%20in%20MIT's%20EECS%20Master%20of%20Engineering%20program%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fregistrar.mit.edu%2Fstatistics-reports%2Fenrollment-statistics-year%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreased%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20241%20students%20for%20the%202023-2024%20academic%20year%20to%20303%20this%20academic%20year%20%E2%80%94%20a%20spike%20compared%20to%20previous%20years%20when%20enrollment%20stayed%20relatively%20consistent%20in%20the%20mid-200s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcgsnet.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F2022-Graduate-Enrollment-and-Degrees-Final-Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Council%20of%20Graduate%20Schools%20said%20that%20computer%20science%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%20field%20to%20increase%20in%20first-time%20enrollment%20(5.4%25)%20between%20Fall%202021%20and%20Fall%202022.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIan%20Hurrel%2C%20who%20is%20finishing%20his%20last%20semester%20at%20Georgia%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20said%20enrolling%20in%20the%20university's%20one-year%20master's%20program%20was%20largely%20due%20to%20the%20worsening%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20including%20me%2C%20wanted%20to%20stay%20in%20college%20one%20more%20year%20to%20get%20an%20internship%2C%26quot%3B%20Hurrel%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20very%20much%20a%20'panic%20masters'%20sort%20of%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20computer%20and%20information%20sciences%20often%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fprograms%2Fcoe%2Findicator%2Fctb%2Fgraduate-degree-fields%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20numbers%20of%20graduate%20enrollment%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20other%20fields%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic1.squarespace.com%2Fstatic%2F6197797102be715f55c0e0a1%2Ft%2F65fb306bc81e0c239fb4f6a9%2F1710960749260%2FTalent%2BDisrupted%2B03052024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Burning%20Glass%20Institute%20indicated%20that%207%25%20of%20those%20who%20earned%20graduate%20degrees%20in%20CS%20remained%20unemployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20extra%20schooling%2C%20while%20costly%2C%20can%20not%20only%20buy%20students%20time%2C%20it%20can%20potentially%20lead%20to%20a%20more%20employable%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20higher%20salary.%20According%20to%20data%20from%20PayScale%20published%20last%20year%2C%20employees%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.payscale.com%2Fresearch%2FUS%2FDegree%3DMaster_of_Science_(MS)%252C_Computer_Science_(CS)%2FSalary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaster%20of%20science%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20an%20average%20base%20salary%20of%20%24112%2C000%2C%20compared%20to%20%2472%2C000%20for%20those%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.payscale.com%2Fresearch%2FUS%2FDegree%3DBachelor%2527s_Degree%252C_Computer_Science_(CS)%2FSalary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebachelor's%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%