scal%20packages%20passed%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20subsequent%20need%20to%20jack%20up%20interest%20rates%20to%20deal%20with%20inflation%20mean%20the%20options%20for%20the%20new%20administration%20are%20somewhat%20limited%20in%20scope.%20Politically%2C%20there%20is%20less%20will%20to%20increase%20the%20deficit%20with%20a%20swath%20of%20new%20measures%2C%20and%20economically%2C%20higher%20interest%20rates%20make%20it%20not%20only%20more%20costly%20to%20enact%20new%20pieces%20of%20legislation%20into%20law%20but%20also%20raise%20the%20risk%20of%20causing%20another%20upturn%20in%20consumer%20prices.%20Nominal%20interest%20rates%20are%20higher%20than%20they%20were%20at%20the%20time%20of%20Bush's%202003%20tax%20cut.%20Of%20course%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20potential%20growth%20was%20not%20thought%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%20it%20is%20now.%20And%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublicans-house-representatives-election-win-majority-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20thin%20GOP%20majority%20in%20the%20House%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Representatives%2C%20it's%20not%20immediately%20obvious%20that%20a%20package%20of%20tax%20and%20spending%20can%20easily%20make%20it%20through%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20options%20does%20the%20Trump%20team%20have%3F%20I%20can%20think%20of%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20ought%20to%20recognize%20that%20the%20age%20of%20abundance%20no%20longer%20exists.%20You%20can't%20do%20everything.%20There%20is%20no%20world%20where%20we%20can%20add%20millions%20of%20new%20homes%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%20and%20reorient%20the%20US%20manufacturing%20sector.%20You%20must%20pick%20and%20choose%20which%20priorities%20are%20the%20most%20important.%20For%20the%20time%20being%2C%20this%20probably%20means%20trying%20to%20phase%20out%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-approve-funding-for-ev-charging-before-trump-takes-office-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancel%20planned%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Biden%20spending%20bills.%20While%20this%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20do%20given%20the%20tight%20Congress%2C%20there%20are%20things%20Trump%20could%20do%20unilaterally.%20One%20target%20could%20be%20the%20roughly%20%24200%20billion%20designated%20for%20the%20Energy%20Department's%20Loan%20Programs%20Office.%20Under%20Biden%2C%20the%20office%20has%20announced%20or%20completed%20nearly%20%2430%20billion%20in%20loans%20or%20loan%20guarantees%20to%2023%20commercial%20projects%2C%20per%20Politico%2C%20supporting%20efforts%20including%20the%20domestic%20supply%20chain%20for%20electric-vehicle%20batteries%2C%20clean%20hydrogen%2C%20and%20replacing%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20steelmaking.%20The%20Trump%20administration%20could%20shut%20off%20the%20spigot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20canceling%20some%20of%20the%20projects%20would%20take%20some%20wind%20out%20of%20America's%20manufacturing%20sails%2C%20taking%20steps%20to%20consolidate%20the%20budget%20would%20likely%20bring%20some%20relief%20to%20the%20bond%20market.%20After%20all%2C%20a%20dramatic%20increase%20in%20government%20outlays%20in%20recent%20years%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20contributed%2C%20at%20least%20in%20part%2C%20to%20the%20run-up%20in%20consumer%20prices%20we've%20seen.%20Politically%2C%20I%20think%20the%20trade-off%20makes%20sense%20for%20Team%20Trump.%20After%20all%2C%20Democrats%20targeted%20this%20spending%20to%20battleground%20states%20like%20Georgia%20and%20Arizona.%20The%20results%20were%20clear%3A%20Economic%20development%20was%20not%20sufficient%20to%20deliver%20the%20states%20to%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris.%20People%20would%20likely%20prefer%20lower%20rates%20instead%20%E2%80%94%20the%20benefits%20are%20more%20widespread.%20Interest%20rates%20are%20a%20blunt%20tool%2C%20having%20a%20broad%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%20and%20financial%20markets.%20And%20with%20affordability%20being%20a%20critical%20issue%20for%20the%20