s%20a%20scam.%20As%20reality%20began%20to%20set%20in%2C%20I%20got%20really%20angry%3B%20I'd%20been%20so%20loyal%20to%20Google.%20I%20loved%20working%20there%20and%20felt%20so%20proud%20to%20be%20there.%20I%20went%20through%20the%20five%20stages%20of%20grief%20and%20wondered%2C%20%3Cem%3EWhy%20me%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20I%20got%20depressed.%20I'd%20look%20at%20my%20empty%20calendar%20and%20feel%20rejected%2C%20like%20nobody%20wanted%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20to%20see%20how%20I%20could%20use%20my%20severance%20package%20as%20an%20opportunity.%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20a%20%26quot%3Bgap%20year%26quot%3B%20and%20wrote%20out%20a%20list%20of%20things%20I'd%20always%20wanted%20to%20do%3A%20work%20at%20Trader%20Joe's%2C%20be%20a%20barista%2C%20work%20at%20In-N-Out%20Burger%2C%20drive%20for%20Lyft%20or%20Uber%2C%20pet%20sit%2C%20work%20as%20a%20bartender.%20It%20made%20me%20feel%20really%20rejuvenated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20first%20weekend%2C%20I%20applied%20to%20Trader%20Joe's.%20But%20on%20my%20first%20day%2C%20I%20had%20trouble%20walking%20in%20the%20door.%20I'd%20been%20the%20director%20at%20a%20big%20company%2C%20was%20a%20two-time%20published%20author%2C%20and%20had%20been%20featured%20on%20a%20top%20Korean%20talk%20show%3B%20I%20thought%20people%20would%20look%20down%20on%20me%20because%20of%20the%20Asian%20cultural%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bsaving%20face.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20an%20internal%20barrier%20I%20had%20to%20break%20through%2C%20and%20I%20did.%20By%20May%2C%20I%20was%20working%20three%20jobs%20at%20the%20same%20time%20for%20up%20to%2070%20hours%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20Trader%20Joe's%2C%20Starbucks%2C%20and%20Lyft%20whenever%20I%20had%20time%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20pet-sitting%20on%20an%20ad%20hoc%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20write%20a%20book%20about%20my%20experience%20to%20motivate%20other%20people%20in%20the%20same%20situation%20as%20me.%20Being%20laid%20off%20is%20painful%20%E2%80%94%20even%20more%20so%20in%20Korean%20culture%20because%20p