p-hts-could-be-removed-from-uks-banned-terror-organisation-list-13270232%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsyrian-rebel-group-hts-could-be-removed-from-uks-banned-terror-organisation-list-13270232%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hyundai%20Motor%20to%20set%20up%20600%20charging%20stations%20for%20EVs%20over%20next%207%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733734040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhyundai-motor-to-set-up-600-charging-stations-for-evs-over-next-7-years-124120900494_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20second-largest%20carmaker%20is%20set%20to%20launch%20its%20first%20mass-market%20electric%20car%2C%20the%20Creta%20EV%2C%20in%20the%20coming%20months%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhyundai-motor-to-set-up-600-charging-stations-for-evs-over-next-7-years-124120900494_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Damascus'%20Nehru%20Street%2C%20Assad's%20Kashmir%20View%3A%20What%20Now%20For%20India-Syria%20Ties%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%201957%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20made%20a%20pitstop%20at%20Syrian%20capital%20Damascus%2C%20on%20his%20way%20to%20the%20United%20States.%20India%20and%20Syria%20had%20established%20diplomatic%20relations%20seven%20years%20earlier%2C%20and%20to%20mark%20that%20friendship%2C%20a%20street%20in%20Damascus'%20historic%20Ummayad%20Square%20was%20named%20'Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20Street'.%20Over%20the%20decades%2C%20this%20relationship%20has%20weathered%20many%20political%20storms%20and%20wars%2C%20however%2C%20with%20the%20fall%20of%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20regime%2C%20questions%20are%20being%20raised%20about%20what%20the%20new%20India-Syria%20relationship%20will%20look%20like.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShared%20Principles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESyria%2C%20under%20the%20Assad%20family%20-%20first%20Hafez%20al-Assad%20and%20later%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20-%20has%20consistently%20supported%20India%20on%20critical%20issues%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20Kashmir.%20While%20many%20Islamic%20nations%20rallied%20around%20Pakistan's%20stance%20on%20Kashmir%2C%20Syria%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20countries%20that%20stood%20apart%2C%20often%20voicing%20its%20support%20for%20India's%20sovereignty.%20The%20Assads'%20secular%20governance%20aligned%20with%20India's%20own%20principles%2C%20creating%20a%20strong%20foundation%20for%20collaboration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20India%20revoked%20Article%20370%20in%202019%2C%20which%20granted%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20special%20autonomy%2C%20the%20Syrian%20government%20unequivocally%20described%20it%20as%20India's%20%26quot%3Binternal%20matter%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERiad%20Abbas%2C%20Syria's%20envoy%20to%20New%20Delhi%20at%20the%20time%2C%20expressed%20unflinching%20support%3A%20%26quot%3BEvery%20government%20has%20the%20right%20to%20do%20whatever%20it%20likes%20on%20its%20land%20to%20protect%20its%20people.%20We%20are%20always%20with%20India%20on%20any%20action.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThreat%20Of%20A%20New%20Order%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBashar%20al-Assad's%20downfall%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20resurgence%20of%20extremist%20groups%20in%20Syria%2C%20presents%20challenges%20for%20India.%20During%20the%20height%20of%20ISIS's%20power%2C%20Syria%20-%20bolstered%20by%20Russian%20and%20Iranian%20support%20-%20dismantled%20the%20terror%20group's%20influence.%20A%20vacuum%20in%20Syrian%20leadership%20could%20see%20extremist%20groups%20regaining%20momentum%2C%20with%20implications%20far%20beyond%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%2C%20the%20revival%20of%20such%20groups%2C%20including%20ISIS%2C%20poses%20a%20direct%20security%20challenge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20current%20political%20turmoil%2C%20India%20has%20urged%20for%20a%20%26quot%3BSyria-led%26quot%3B%20process%20to%20bring%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20monitoring%20the%20situation%20in%20Syria%20in%20the%20light%20of%20on-going%20developments.%20We%20underline%20the%20need%20for%20all%20parties%20to%20work%20towards%20preserving%20the%20unity%2C%20sovereignty%20and%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20Syria.%20We%20advocate%20a%20peaceful%20and%20inclusive%20Syrian-led%20political%20process%20respecting%20the%20interests%20and%20aspirations%20of%20all%20sections%20of%20Syrian%20society.%20Our%20Embassy%20in%20Damascus%20is%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20Indian%20community%2C%20for%20their%20safety%20and%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Diplomatic%20Stance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20consistently%20championed%20a%20Syrian-led%20resolution%20to%20the%20conflict%20in%20accordance%20with%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council.%20India%20has%20maintained%20its%20embassy%20in%20Damascus%2C%20even%20during%20the%20peak%20of%20Syria's%20civil%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20historically%20supported%20Syria's%20claims%20over%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20-%20contested%20by%20Israel.%20In%202010%2C%20former%20President%20Pratibha%20Patil%20visited%20Damascus%20and%20reiterated%20that%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia%20has%20consistently%20supported%20all%20just%20Arab%20causes.%20I%20would%20like%20to%20reiterate%20India's%20unwavering%20support%20for%20a%20lasting%20and%20comprehensive%20peace%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%20problem%2C%20based%20on%20relevant%20UN%20resolutions.%20I%20would%20also%20like%20to%20reiterate%20our%20strong%20support%20for%20Syria's%20legitimate%20right%20to%20the%20Golan%20Heights%2C%20and%20for%20its%20very%20early%20and%20full%20return%20to%20Syria%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Patil%20had%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20And%20Cultural%20Ties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20diplomacy%2C%20economic%20and%20cultural%20exchanges%20have%20been%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20India-Syria%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20visited%20Syria%20and%20signed%20MoUs%20on%20biotechnology%2C%20small%20industries%2C%20and%20education.%20India%20provided%20a%20%2425%20million%20line%20of%20credit%20and%20a%20%241%20million%20grant%20for%20a%20biotechnology%20centre%20in%20Damascus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20visited%20India%2C%20where%20he%20endorsed%20plans%20for%20agricultural%20cooperation%20and%20studies%20on%20Syria's%20phosphate%20resources.%20India%20offered%20to%20establish%20an%20IT%20Center%20of%20Excellence%20in%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20former%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20External%20Affairs%2C%20V%20Muraleedharan%2C%20met%20with%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20and%20discussed%20bilateral%20ties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrade%20between%20the%20two%20nations%20has%20also%20flourished.%20Indian%20exports%20to%20Syria%20have%20included%20textiles%2C%20machinery%2C%20and%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20while%20imports%20have%20focused%20on%20raw%20materials%20such%20as%20rock%20phosphate%20and%20cotton.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733733480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fsiu7ftco_india-syria-_625x300_09_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-bashar-al-assads-fall-means-for-historic-india-syria-relations-7206308%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Syria%2C%20under%20the%20Assad%20family%20-%20first%20Hafez%20al-Assad%20and%20later%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20-%20has%20consistently%20supported%20India%20on%20critical%20issues%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20Kashmir.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%