%20out%20loud%2C%20so%20the%20police%20would%20know%20that%20school-going%2C%20regular%20children%20lived%20there.%20I%20always%20found%20this%20so%20strange.%20Why%20were%20we%20constantly%20told%20to%20hide%2C%20to%20run%3F%20What%20crime%20had%20we%20committed%20that%20made%20us%20feel%20that%20our%20existence%20was%20dishonest%3F%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Naseema%20Khatoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%2C%2039%2C%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20a%20red-light%20area%2C%20experiencing%20firsthand%20the%20stigma%20and%20neglect%20faced%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F350204%2Fsandhya-nair-kranti-ngo-daughters-of-sex-workers-kamathipura-international-university%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esex%20workers%20and%20their%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Today%2C%20having%20broken%20free%20from%20the%20cycle%20of%20poverty%2C%20she%20has%20become%20a%20powerful%20voice%20for%20the%20marginalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20was%20enrolled%20in%20school%20that%20I%20developed%20a%20sense%20of%20inquisitiveness%20about%20my%20identity.%20I%20would%20be%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20people%20would%20ask%20me%20my%20full%20name%20and%20where%20I%20was%20from.%20But%20I%20was%20told%20not%20to%20tell%20people%20where%20I%20lived%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcampaign.thebetterindia.com%2Fbetapadhaodeshjagao%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22BetaPadhaoDeshJagao%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FBetaPadhaoDeshJagao-desktop-1732080268.jpg%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fa%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELife%20in%20a%20red-light%2