ng%20another%20baby%2C%20but%20by%20the%20time%20we%20got%20married%2C%20my%20son%20was%20already%208%20years%20old.%20That%20meant%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-it-usually-takes-couples-to-get-pregnant-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eeven%20if%20I%20got%20pregnant%20right%20away%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20my%20son%20would%20be%20nearly%2010%20by%20the%20time%20I%20had%20another%20baby.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommon-newborn-baby-myths-post-pregnancy-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20a%20newborn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20a%20nearly%2010-year-old%20boy%20seemed%20like%20what%20would%20be%20a%20large%20gap%20between%20siblings.%20Plus%2C%20with%20my%20son%20getting%20closer%20and%20closer%20to%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20the%20thought%20of%20having%20to%20start%20over%20again%20with%20another%20baby%20was%20more%20depressing%20than%20anything%20else.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20halfway%20to%20the%20finish%20line%2C%20and%20the%20thought%20of%20beginning%20again%20from%20square%20one%20was%20not%20appealing.%20The%20older%20my%20son%20got%2C%20the%20closer%20I%20was%20to%20being%20%26quot%3Bdone%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20felt%20like%20a%20relief.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22911b3970-a449-4cfd-b1a6-86ba1f30a402%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20being%20a%20mom%2C%20I%20was%20already%20so%20tired%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20been%20a%20single%20mom%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20and%20while%20I%20still%20look%20back%20fondly%20at%20that%20time%20of%20my%20life%20when%20it%20was%20just%20my%20son%20and%20I%2C%20I%20found%20motherhood%20to%20be%20exhausting.%20I%20sometimes%20wonder%20how%20I%20accomplished%20taking%20care%20of%20the%20two%20of%20us%20all%20on%20my%20own%2C%20and%20the%20only%20answer%20I%20come%20up%20with%20is%20survival.%20I%20can%20remember%20thinking%20when%20my%20son%20was%20born%20that%20I%20would%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fnewborn-sleep%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enever%20sleep%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20while%20that%20isn't%20true%2C%20I%20certainly%20never%20slept%20in%20late%20again.%20Even%20before%20I%20met%20my%20husband%2C%20I%20was%20already%20so%20burnt%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUltimately%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20not%20to%20have%20a%20child%20together.%20One%20of%20the%20main%20reasons%20that%20contributed%20to%20our%20decision%20was%20that%20parenting%20my%20son%20was%20already%20a%20lot%20of%20work.%20While%20I%20had%20already%20parented%20solo%20for%20years%2C%20he%20had%20become%20an%20overnight%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstepdad-shares-how-he-became-part-of-his-stepchildrens-lives-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvolved%20stepdad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20are%20on%20the%20same%20page%20in%20that%20parenting%20is%20a%20full%20time%20job%20on%20top%20of%20our%20careers%2C%20so%20there%20is%20little%20to%20no%20time%20left%20for%20us%20to%20rest.%20When%20we%20aren't%20working%20outside%20of%20the%20home%2C%20we%20are%20at%20home%20working%20as%20parents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d9e8f796-3ed0-4c6a-9a16-08eb07411840%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20well%20into%20our%2030s%20by%20the%20time%20we%20found%20each%20other%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20our%20age%20played%20a%20factor%20in%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20deciding%20not%20to%20have%20a%20baby%20together.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20I%20already%20had%20a%20child%20when%20we%20started%20dating%2C%20he%20and%20I%20have%20never%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20experience%20our%20relationship%20outside%20of%20being%20parents.%20When%20my%20son%20graduates%20from%20high%20school%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20will%20both%20be%20in%20our%20mid-40s.%20If%20we%20had%20decided%20to%20have%20another%20baby%20when%20we%20got%20married%2C%20we%20would%20each%20be%20almost%2060%20by%20the%20time%20that%20child%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-new-us-graduates-work-high-school-level-jobs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egraduated%20from%20high%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20we%20are%20still%20relatively%20young%2C%20we%20want%20to%20experience%20life%20as%20a%20couple%20without%20kids.%20We%20want%20to%20spend%20our%20time%20working%20less%20and%20traveling%20more%20as%20soon%20as%20we%20possibly%20can.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22997bf7e4-3e7e-4ef6-9424-51283f4a3f92%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EInitially%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20leaned%20more%20towards%20having%20a%20baby%20than%20not%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20wanted%20to%20experience%20having%20a%20child%20with%20a%20supportive%20partner%2C%20while%20I%20think%20my%20husband%20didn't%20want%20to%20miss%20out%20on%20having%20his%20own%20child.%20So%20I%20was%20nervous%20to%20introduce%20my%20hesitation%20to%20have%20another%20baby%20into%20our%20conversation%20about%20having%20kids.%20But%20I'm%20glad%20I%20was%20brave%20enough%20to%20ask%20him%20to%20entertain%20the%20idea%20of%20what%20our%20life%20would%20be%20like%20without%20having%20another%20child.%20Until%20I%20brought%20it%20up%20as%20an%20alternative%2C%20he%20said%20he%20hadn't%20really%20thought%20much%20about%20life%20without%20a%20baby.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20always%20felt%20like%20I'm%20not%20allowed%20to%20say%20how%20much%20work%20being%20a%20mom%20can%20be.%20For%20a%20long%20time%2C%20I%20felt%20ashamed%20for%20being%20exhausted%20by%20parenting.%20I%20always%20felt%20that%20the%20expectation%20was%20to%20have%20more%20than%20one%20child.%20When%20I%20found%20my%20husband%2C%20many%20people%20assumed%20that%20having%20a%20baby%20together%20would%20be%20the%20next%20step%2C%20and%20I%20know%20he%20felt%20that%20expectation%20as%20well.%20We're%20both%20glad%20that%20we%20allowed%20ourselves%20to%20even%20consider%20not%20having%20a%20baby%2C%20because%20in%20thinking%20carefully%20about%20that%2C%20we%20realized%20that%20having%20another%20child%20wasn't%20what%20we%20wanted.%20It%20was%20what%20others%20expected%20of%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20once%20in%20a%20while%20I'll%20think%20about%20what%20it%20would%20be%20like%20to%20have%20another%20baby.%20Mostly%20it's%20when%20I%20walk%20by%20an%20adorable%20set%20of%20footie%20pajamas%20in%20a%20store%20or%20encounter%20a%20storybook%20that%20I%20loved%20reading%20to%20my%20son.%20While%20on%20one%20hand%20it%20does%20feel%20sad%20that%20I'll%20never%20have%20a%20baby%20again%2C%20I%20always%20circle%20back%20to%20the%20same%20conclusion%2C%20and%20that%20is%20that%20we%20made%20the%20right%20decision.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20my%20son%20brings%20the%20fulfillment%20to%20our%20lives%20that%20being%20a%20parent%20can%20provide%2C%20but%20footie%20pajamas%20are%20not%20a%20strong%20enough%20reason%20to%20have%20another%20child.%20I%20am%20no%20longer%20ashamed%20to%20admit%20that%20I'm%20already%20too%20tired%20for%20a%20second%20child.%20While%20being%20a%20mom%20is%20something%20I'm%20proud%20of%2C%20I%20am%20also%20very%20much%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20next%20part%20of%20my%20life%20once%20my%20son%20is%20grown.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkid-will-be-an-only-child-i